 &#10;-- bussing to and from school, though parents might have paid for a portion of this, I'm not sure &#10;^^Those are all funds out of an entirely different pot of money. Textbooks are paid for out of the district's budget, SPED services are paid for out of the district's budget, as well as by the state and federal goverment, and bussing is paid for out of the transportation budget. Attendance money is paid on a daily basis by the state - this is why schools are so big on attendance, tardies, and absences. If your kid isn't in the seat by x:xx, then the school misses out on that money from your child. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="907" language="en" documentId="655" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Carbon Copy" date="09/06/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=37" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="655" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="71"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="72" end="304"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="305" end="403"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="404" end="907"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>